posts.description: Come feast with us 🤗 On May 14th I'll be hosting a 3-course Sunday lunch with the amazing eco-chef @tomsfeast in our pop up Garden in Exchange square. The menu for this is incredible and we've really worked hard to create something which celebrates delicious, seasonal British produce for you all to enjoy! Tickets are available in the events section of deliciouslyella.com, can't wait to see you there 😘
Yay for bank holiday weekends 🤗 Enjoying extra time for sleep, walks with @mr_austin_mills and time with Matt 👫🐶❤️

😍😍😍 Couldn't resist sharing one more of this guy, because I really love him ❤️ Look at that crumbly oaty top, the sweet berries oozing out and the melted raspberry ripple ice cashew ice cream 😋Recipe on deliciouslyella.com 👀

A bank holiday apple and berry tart is on the blog for you now 🤗 Its filled with a fruity blend of blueberries, raspberries and apple with a vanilla infused based and a crumbly oat top... and the good news is that it's nut free too! I made the recipe for @bupaglobal and as so many of you ask us for nut-free recipes, I wanted to share it here too - I hope this makes you guys really happy 😊Recipe on deliciouslyella.com 👀

Guess who's turning two today... Only the sassy little guy in this photo @mr_austin_mills ❤️ Would you look at his face, it's my favourite thing ever 😂 Wishing a very happy birthday to the king 👑Pic by the amazing @sophia_spring_photography 📸

Quick lunch from the deli on the run today 💃My favourite new black rice and aubergine salad; our broccoli, kohlrabi and cashew mix; maple roasted sweet potatoes and some roasted cauliflower falafels 🤗
Loving breakfast even more than usual today with this granola, coconut yoghurt, apple and berry compote and a squeeze of honey 😋

I know what I'm making for dinner tonight 🤗 All the ingredients looking beautiful for my sautéed sesame and aubergine noodle bowl 🙌🏻 It sounds fancy but it just takes ten mins to make, so it's a real winner for a weekday supper ☺️ Link to the recipe in my bio, or head straight to deliciouslyella.com 👀

We've been doing loads of recipe testing in the office this week and this one is my favourite so far... sautéed garlic, tamari, chilli flakes and sesame oil with little bites of aubergine, sliced mushrooms and broccoli, tons of noodles and a good sprinkling of chives, toasted cashews and sesame seeds. The recipe is online now, just head over to deliciouslyella.com or click the link in my bio to check it out, and let me know what you think if you make it 🤗
These beauties in our Herne Hill deli brightening up my day 🌸
When your lunch is so delicious you're not sure one bowl will be enough 😉 Feasting on the most incredible creamy pasta with spaghetti, lots of mushrooms and fresh parsley today👌🏼
Afternoon pick me up ☺️ Coconut milk with turmeric, cinnamon and a squeeze of honey 💖

A favourite lunch to start the week... my warm roasted carrot salad with red onions, lentils, toasted pine nuts and lots of herbs. The recipe is an old favourite from the blog 🤗 Link for the recipe is in my bio 🙌🏼

This was as we exchanged our rings and made it all official 💖 Matt asked me my thoughts on marriage on our first date and I said I wasn't sure I ever wanted to get married... two weeks later we were living together and I knew all I wanted was to be with him forever ☺️After 4 months we were engaged, got @mr_austin_mills and had started a business together - the whole thing has been quite the whirlwind 🤗 People thought we were mad (with good reason!) but I've never seen so sure about anything 🎉

One year ago today 👰🏻💖👨🏻💍🍾💒🎊❤️We were standing barefoot on the beach, saying I do - I was half laughing, half crying the whole way through, and it was completely magical ☺️I feel incredibly lucky to have such a special, supportive person by my side - I've learnt so much from him since we've been together and feel constantly inspired by his unbelievably kind and optimistic view on life. Here's to many more happy years and lots of anniversaries in the future 😍
